U.S. Agriculture Secretary Richard Lyng ask Japan offer share rice market U.S. exporter visit country month. In interview Reuters Lyng Reagan administration ask Tokyo remove quota U.S. beef citrus exports. Lyng plan Japan April 14-27 ask Tokyo liberalize fully rice market. "We urge consider share rice market" said. The USDA secretary share Japanese rice market U.S. request. "We've none now. If cent improvement" said. Last Reagan administration reject petition U.S. rice industry seek relief Japanese import restrictions. However U.S. reexamine issue mid-1987 Japan roll import barrier U.S. rice exports. Lyng conduct formal negotiation month Japan beef citrus quota visit "may forerunner way" talk prior expiration bilateral agreement March 1988. He U.S. "will ask definite liberalization item (beef citrus).... When translate 'liberalization' Japanese mean quota." Reuter 